    <chapter title="Beginner Course Overview" id="basic-course-overview" collapsible="true">
        <p>In the beginner course, you will kickstart your skills by creating a custom domino project.</p>
        <procedure title="CAD / CAM Basics">
            <step>Create a basic domino model, with constraints in mind</step>
            <step>Generate proper toolpaths that can easily be run</step>
        </procedure>
        <procedure title="Machine Safety">
            <step>Learn the proper safety procedures and protocols, in order to keep yourself and the equipment safe</step>
        </procedure>
        <procedure title="Machine and Software Outline">
            <step>Learn the outline of the machine's buttons, switches, and inputs.</step>
            <step>Learn how to start up and shut down the machine</step>
            <step>Learn the basics of the Tormach PathPilot Software and interface</step>
        </procedure>
        <procedure title="Basic Fixturing and Operation">
            <step>Learn how to jog, change tools, and load operations</step>
            <step>Learn proper methods to secure your part to the machine</step>
            <step>Learn how to manually find part zeroes</step>
            <step>Learn how to run your operations safely and effectively</step>
        </procedure>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Intermediate Course Overview" id="inter-course-overview" collapsible="true">
        <p>In the intermediate course, you will create a custom multipart design to be machined.</p>
        <procedure title="Advanced CAM">
            <step>Lean how to know if your model is machinable</step>
            <step>Learn advanced operations in CAM</step>
            <step>Learn how to manipulate toolpaths to your constraints</step>
        </procedure>
        <procedure title="In-depth PathPilot">
            <step>Learn more advanced interfaces and options within PathPilot</step>
        </procedure>
        <procedure title="Intermediate Fixturing and Operation">
            <step>Learn to determine the proper way to fixture your part</step>
            <step>Learn how to use the viewport to determine information about your processes</step>
        </procedure>
    </chapter>

    <chapter title="Advanced Course Overview" id="adv-course-overview" collapsible="true">
        <p>In the Advanced course, you will create a chess piece with both the CNC lathe and the mill.</p>
        <procedure title="Offshoot: Basics of the Lathe">
            <step>You will be directed to the beginner lathe course, and use your previous knowledge of the mill to create the body of a chess piece.</step>
        </procedure>
        <procedure title="Probing and Advanced Workholding">
            <step>Learn how to use the active probe to more easily find stock positions, especially with circular parts</step>
            <step>Lean how to use a collet block to allow yourself to mill circular parts</step>
        </procedure>
    </chapter>
